Both outputs are emitted in the working directory:

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 100 hypotheses, 100 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`. Top-level fields set: `dataset_id=ds001_aml`, `model_id=claude-opus-4-7`, `harness_id=claude-code-manual@2026-04`, `max_iterations=25`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative walkthrough of supported, unsupported, and mixed findings.

**Headline findings:**
- ECOG performance status dominates ORR (OR 0.68/unit, p ≈ 1e-97).
- IDH1 mutation strongly raises ORR (adj OR 1.43, p ≈ 1e-17) — biggest biomarker signal.
- Disease burden (blast %, WBC, weight loss, CRP) and nutrition (albumin) all behave as expected.
- Two real interactions: complex karyotype × 7+3 negative (p = 0.0016); unfit × venaza positive (p = 0.036).
- All four matched-targeted-therapy interactions (FLT3+mido, FLT3+gilt, IDH1+ivo, IDH2+ena) are null or negative — likely indication-channelling on this observational ORR endpoint. Composite matched-therapy effect is also null.
- TP53, complex karyotype alone, age, NPM1, most comorbidities and SNPs are null on ORR.
